om\": 1881, \"to\": 2005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Germany thrashed Zambia 4-1 in St. Etienne with a brace from Lea Schueller and goals from Klara Buehl and Elisa Senss to clinch a spot in the next round with a second place finish in Group B.  Schueller opened the scoring for the 2016 gold medalists 10 minutes in before Bruhl doubled the advantage from long-range two minutes after the break.\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2007, \"end\": 2014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998192424918, \"rank\": 1.8075760109088554e-07, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2068, \"end\": 2071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Salonga\", \"score\": 0.9997459450798002, \"rank\": 0.00023848917860924972, \"text\": \"Lea\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Salonga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Salonga\"}, {\"begin\": 2097, \"end\": 2102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klara_Prast\", \"score\": 0.9999998082680761, \"rank\": 1.917319201841116e-07, \"text\": \"Klara\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klara_Prast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klara_Prast\"}, {\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ELIZA\", \"score\": 0.9763288318189279, \"rank\": 0.024044745868143855, \"text\": \"Elisa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ELIZA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ELIZA\"}, {\"begin\": 2190, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_FIFA_World_Cup_Group_B\", \"score\": 0.9999999999979536, \"rank\": 2.0